    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Centre Hospitalier Universitaire Dijon</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this retrospective study is to show that kyphoplasty is a reliable technique in
      the treatment of certain traumatic vertebral fractures.

      Patients will be selected from medical records archived at the Neuroradiology Department of
      Dijon CHU.

      An information sheet and questionnaire will be sent to patients together with a letter to ask
      them to have a radiographic examination.

      The radiographic images will be interpreted by two independent experts to evaluate the angle
      pf vertebral kyphosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
